      <p>In the following, two genes of a given species are said to be <italic>neighboring</italic> if they are separated by at most three other genes on the same strand of the same chromosome.</p>
      <sec id="Sec12">
        <title>Trail grouping by reactions</title>
        <p>Briefly, the method of grouping trails by reactions consists in grouping reactions of the reference species according to the reaction sets they belong to. This grouping method focuses more on metabolic rather than genomic conserved patterns.</p>
